- Hi, Billy. How are you?
- How are you?

20:45.000 --> 20:46.960
Hi, hi. This is Tom Fiedler
from the <i>Miami Herald.</i>

20:47.040 --> 20:48.918
Miami. Yes, I can tell by your tie.

20:49.000 --> 20:50.798
That's Miami, all right.

20:50.880 --> 20:53.031
Thank you. Really appreciate it.
Thank you.

20:53.120 --> 20:54.456
A small army
of reporters and photographers...

20:54.480 --> 20:56.073
At least 20 or 30 cameras

20:56.160 --> 20:57.576
- or 50 or 60 reporters.
- Three, two, one.

20:57.600 --> 21:01.435
<i>I intend, as I always have,
to run a campaign of ideas.</i>

21:02.000 --> 21:03.150
<i>Ideas have power.</i>

21:03.880 --> 21:05.792
Ideas are what governing is all about,

21:05.880 --> 21:09.078
and governing is what
this election is all about.

21:09.360 --> 21:12.398
<i>Standing before the snow-capped
Rocky Mountains in Colorado,</i>

21:12.480 --> 21:14.392
<i>Gary Hart announced for the presidency.</i>

21:14.480 --> 21:16.756
<i>Nowhere is Hart as much a front runner</i>

21:16.840 --> 21:20.834
<i>as he is in his own hometown,
Ottawa, Kansas.</i>

21:20.920 --> 21:22.513
<i>The former senator from Colorado</i>

21:22.600 --> 21:24.831
<i>arrived at the airport just
about an hour and a half ago.</i>

21:27.200 --> 21:28.520
Now, we're rolling here.

21:32.920 --> 21:36.470
In an era of great change,
challenge and opportunity,

21:36.560 --> 21:37.994
it's less important that our...

21:38.080 --> 21:40.470
