22:16.240 --> 22:17.976
Irene's right.
I'm not writing off the South.

22:18.000 --> 22:21.118
If my ideas make sense in Youngstown,
they'll make sense in Mobile.

22:22.560 --> 22:24.313
Then we get to go to Alabama.

22:24.720 --> 22:28.077
<i>Gary Hart prepares for another busy day
on the campaign trail.</i>

22:28.200 --> 22:31.671
<i>No matter what the most hardened
political cynics may say,</i>

22:32.160 --> 22:33.310
<i>Gary Hart's speech here</i>

22:33.400 --> 22:37.360
<i>was not simply about furthering
his own presidential ambitions.</i>

22:37.440 --> 22:38.635
<i>Take two.</i>

22:38.840 --> 22:40.797
<i>Gary Hart was campaigning
in New England today...</i>

22:40.920 --> 22:43.355
<i>Gary Hart is back in the race
and back in New Hampshire...</i>

22:43.440 --> 22:46.990
<i>It was typical of what you might see
