23:00.680 --> 23:03.096
Let's forget about jobs for a second.
Let's talk about security.

23:03.120 --> 23:06.477
<i>Gary Hart is running far ahead
of the pack of contenders.</i>

23:06.560 --> 23:08.677
<i>- Give me another take.
- Serious campaigning aside,</i>

23:08.760 --> 23:10.080
<i>Hart's mood in recent days...</i>

23:10.200 --> 23:12.954
<i>This week's issue of</i> Newsweek <i>magazine
profiles Hart.</i>

23:13.040 --> 23:14.616
<i>...considered to be
the leading contender</i>

23:14.640 --> 23:16.176
<i>for the Democratic
presidential nomination.</i>

23:16.200 --> 23:17.873
<i>Hart spoke at four schools,</i>

23:18.000 --> 23:20.276
<i>was interviewed
by the editors of two newspapers...</i>

23:20.360 --> 23:21.680
<i>After a blistering first week,</i>

23:21.760 --> 23:24.559
<i>Senator Hart is taking a break
from the campaign trail.</i>

23:39.480 --> 23:40.800
<i>So, he comes to me, he says,</i>

23:40.880 --> 23:43.714
"Hey, Mr. B.B., if I go for that deal,

23:43.800 --> 23:45.996
"I will trade you the car
and the crawfish."

