call your judgment as a leader
into question?

01:35:15.960 --> 01:35:18.634
Yes, I suppose I have...

01:35:18.720 --> 01:35:21.474
I've made some mistakes, but I think...

01:35:21.560 --> 01:35:23.791
Judgment, like character,
needs to be measured

01:35:23.880 --> 01:35:25.712
in the full context of a career,

01:35:25.800 --> 01:35:28.190
and I think what
I've undertaken in the Senate

01:35:28.280 --> 01:35:30.670
and the plans I've outlined
for the country also speak

01:35:30.760 --> 01:35:31.796
to my judgment.

01:35:34.800 --> 01:35:36.029
David. Yes.

01:35:37.200 --> 01:35:39.456
How are you going to convince people
in the Democratic Party

01:35:39.480 --> 01:35:41.915
that you are not going to make
this kind of mistake again?

01:35:42.400 --> 01:35:44.471
By not making
this kind of mistake again.

01:35:46.440 --> 01:35:48.557
- Yes.
- Were there two people in the house?

01:35:48.680 --> 01:35:50.433
Three people? Did they go and come back?

01:35:50.520 --> 01:35:52.830
Alan, we've been through this.
It's on the record.

01:35:53.320 --> 01:35:55.073
There were three people
who came to my house

01:35:55.160 --> 01:35:56.753
on the Saturday, late afternoon,

01:35:56.840 --> 01:35:58.752
and over the course
of maybe two or three hours,

01:35:58.840 --> 01:36:01.309
we left, we came back,
and then they moved on. Yes.

01:36:03.040 --> 01:36:05.874
Senator, you were once quoted
as saying that you love danger.

01:36:05.960 --> 01:36:08.077
Is that why you've put yourself
in this position?

01:36:08.160 --> 01:36:10.436
I don't love it that much, Jack,
trust me.

01:36:12.600 --> 01:36:13.600
Yes.

01:36:14.600 --> 01:36:17.798
Senator Hart, what would you say
to the women voters of this country?

01:36:19.200 --> 01:36:20.475
Well, I would say that,

01:36:20.560 --> 01:36:22.517
if you speak to anyone
who's worked for me,

01:36:22.600 --> 01:36:25.160
my campaign staff, anyone in the Senate,

01:36:25.240 --> 01:36:28.074
over the last 15 to 20 years,
you'll find that I have

01:36:28.160 --> 01:36:31.119
a very healthy relationship,
working relationship with women.

01:36:32.800 --> 01:36:34.393
You said there's no relationship.

01:36:34.480 --> 01:36:36.631
Are you willing to take
a lie detector test?

01:36:38.160 --> 01:36:40.675
I think the voters are
a pretty good lie detector test.

01:36:40.760 --> 01:36:42.416
- Will they believe you?
- I think they do.

01:36:42.440 --> 01:36:44.636
The last poll I saw said
that most voters believe

01:36:44.720 --> 01:36:46.120
the <i>Herald</i> was out of line.

01:36:46.200 --> 01:36:48.669
- More than 60%, in fact.
- 64%.

01:36:49.360 --> 01:36:51.536
Right. When the numbers are in
your favor, always be specific.

01:36:51.560 --> 01:36:52.630
Right?

01:36:54.920 --> 01:36:56.354
Senator? Senator?

01:36:56.440 --> 01:36:58.397
Mr. Parker.

01:36:59.560 --> 01:37:01.472
- Yes, Senator. Thank you.
- Yeah.

01:37:01.560 --> 01:37:02.596
Good afternoon.

01:37:02.680 --> 01:37:03.875
Glad you could make it.

01:37:03.960 --> 01:37:05.189
Yes.

01:37:06.960 --> 01:37:09.280
Yesterday in your speech,
you raised the issue of morality.

01:37:09.960 --> 01:37:12.395
I'd like to ask you, specifically,
what you meant by that.

01:37:12.480 --> 01:37:16.030
I have a series of questions,
if that's all right, if you don't mind.

01:37:17.240 --> 01:37:18.356
All right.

01:37:20.360 --> 01:37:22.238
When you said you did nothing immoral,

01:37:22.320 --> 01:37:24.789
were you referring to that
you had no sexual relationship

01:37:24.880 --> 01:37:29.113
with Donna Rice last week
and/or at any other time?

01:37:31.600 --> 01:37:33.176
Yeah, I've said
there was no relationship.

01:37:33.200 --> 01:37:34.429
That's correct.

01:37:35.880 --> 01:37:39.669
Do you believe adultery is immoral?

01:37:41.280 --> 01:37:42.714
Do I...

01:37:42.800 --> 01:37:44.757
Well, yes. Yes, I do.

01:37:45.160 --> 01:37:46.879
But, Senator...

01:37:49.520 --> 01:37:52.354
Senator, have you
ever committed adultery?

01:37:57.800 --> 01:37:58.800
I...

01:38:02.800 --> 01:38:04.519
Say it. Say it.

01:38:07.200 --> 01:38:08.395
Well...

01:38:11.840 --> 01:38:13.115
I guess...

01:38:13.800 --> 01:38:17.316
I guess I don't think
that that is a fair question.

01:38:50.720 --> 01:38:52.677
- Anyone for more coffee?
- It's early.

01:38:52.760 --> 01:38:53.955
Yeah, I'll have a cup.

01:38:54.040 --> 01:38:55.520
- Sir?
- Yeah, I'll do it.

01:38:56.080 --> 01:38:58.037
- Ma'am?
- No, thank you.

01:38:58.640 --> 01:39:00.480
- Yeah, I'll have one, thank you.
- Yes, ma'am.

01:39:00.520 --> 01:39:02.876
And, you, sir? Coffee?

01:39:03.800 --> 01:39:05.234
Gary?

01:39:05.320 --> 01:39:07.755
- You want a coffee?
- No.

01:39:07.840 --> 01:39:09.200
I need some time with the senator.

01:39:09.240 --> 01:39:10.959
- Are you fucking kidding me?
- Come on.

01:39:11.040 --> 01:39:13.600
You know what?
I tried coke while I was at Berkeley,

01:39:13.680 --> 01:39:16.434
and I cheated on my girlfriend. Twice.

01:39:16.520 --> 01:39:17.920
Just to save you some time.

01:39:18.000 --> 01:39:20.356
Maybe we move up military reform.

01:39:20.440 --> 01:39:21.874
Yeah. We can do a big roll-out,

01:39:21.960 --> 01:39:24.191
- get some generals on board.
- I need to call Andrea.

01:39:24.280 --> 01:39:26.670
- Do you have a dime?
- I have one.

01:39:26.760 --> 01:39:28.194
Do you have change?

01:39:28.280 --> 01:39:30.158
- Yeah. I have a quarter.
- Thank you.

01:39:30.240 --> 01:39:32.536
Look, I'm all for going back out there,
shaking more hands.

01:39:32.560 --> 01:39:35.240
It's just, at the moment, I don't think
we can get the senator to...

01:39:36.360 --> 01:39:38.096
I don't think it's safe
to put him in front of a crowd.

01:39:38.120 --> 01:39:39.696
We could call Denver,
get some more bodies.

01:39:39.720 --> 01:39:41.518
We can book some more TV time.

01:39:41.600 --> 01:39:43.616
I mean, how long would it take
to shoot a 30-minute spot?

01:39:43.640 --> 01:39:45.199
Can we pay for that?

01:39:45.600 --> 01:39:48.638
You know, it's, like, we go out there,
we go right to the voters.

01:39:48.720 --> 01:39:51.599
Irene, is there any...
Any word from Miami?

01:39:52.440 --> 01:39:53.794
How do you mean?

01:39:54.200 --> 01:39:56.032
Is she... Is she okay?

01:39:59.280 --> 01:40:01.636
I don't know how you
want me to answer that.

01:40:02.000 --> 01:40:03.593
Congratulations.

01:40:04.320 --> 01:40:05.879
You just became the <i>National Enquirer.</i>

01:40:05.960 --> 01:40:07.633
You're 50 cents at the register.

01:40:07.720 --> 01:40:10.792
I'm just not sure
enough people would see it.

01:40:10.880 --> 01:40:12.473
If the media's been talking about it...

01:40:13.200 --> 01:40:14.680
We'd need a national buy.

01:40:14.760 --> 01:40:15.910
Where the fuck is Dixon?

01:40:16.000 --> 01:40:17.480
It's outrageous.

01:40:25.560 --> 01:40:27.153
Okay, but you're safe?

01:40:34.080 --> 01:40:35.150
Well...

01:40:37.680 --> 01:40:41.356
They cannot hound you like this.
They will not hound you like this.

01:40:42.400 --> 01:40:45.359
You know what?
They shouldn't even be near you.

01:40:51.200 --> 01:40:53.157
Okay, we will take care of this.

01:41:03.320 --> 01:41:04.549
Lee.

01:41:06.200 --> 01:41:07.919
It's time to go home.

01:41:38.640 --> 01:41:40.950
<i>Tonight, Gary Hart and his wife
are back in Denver,</i>

01:41:41.040 --> 01:41:43.316
<i>where he will end
his latest run for the White House.</i>

01:41:43.400 --> 01:41:45.517
<i>Once considered the man to beat in '88,</i>

01:41:45.600 --> 01:41:48.832
<i>Hart plans to end his candidacy
in a formal announcement at noon.</i>

01:41:52.480 --> 01:41:54.320
Senator Hart, will you
be leaving the campaign?

01:42:06.520 --> 01:42:07.670
<i>Well, clearly,</i>

01:42:07.760 --> 01:42:10.753
<i>under present circumstances,
this campaign cannot go on.</i>

01:42:13.480 --> 01:42:16.632
<i>I refuse to submit
my family and my friends</i>

01:42:16.720 --> 01:42:18.518
<i>to further rumors and gossip.</i>

01:42:22.360 --> 01:42:24.795
<i>I don't want to be the issue,</i>

01:42:24.880 --> 01:42:27.793
<i>and I cannot be the issue.</i>

01:42:28.680 --> 01:42:30.751
<i>If you're gonna
have to spend all your time</i>

01:42:30.840 --> 01:42:32.035
<i>talking about yourself</i>

01:42:32.120 --> 01:42:34.840
<i>and you're not particularly
good at that anyway,</i>

01:42:34.960 --> 01:42:37.919
<i>then you can't maintain
the link with the voters.</i>

01:42:42.760 --> 01:42:45.070
<i>In public life,
some things may be interesting,</i>

01:42:45.160 --> 01:42:48.232
<i>but that doesn't necessarily
mean they're important.</i>

01:42:49.080 --> 01:42:50.833
<i>And the farmers in Amarillo,</i>

01:42:50.920 --> 01:42:53.879
<i>the oil field workers in Louisiana,</i>

01:42:53.960 --> 01:42:56.429
<i>the steelworkers in Pennsylvania,</i>

01:42:56.520 --> 01:42:58.477
<i>they wantjobs.</i>

01:42:58.560 --> 01:43:01.473
<i>Their kids want an education,
and like all the rest of us,</i>

01:43:01.560 --> 01:43:04.519
<i>they don't want to be killed
by some nuclear weapon.</i>

01:43:06.640 --> 01:43:09.314
Now, we're all gonna have
to seriously question the system

01:43:09.400 --> 01:43:11.790
we have for electing
our national leaders,

01:43:11.880 --> 01:43:14.395
that has reporters in bushes,

01:43:14.480 --> 01:43:17.473
photographers peeking in our windows,

01:43:17.560 --> 01:43:20.758
that reduces the press of this nation
into the hunters

01:43:20.880 --> 01:43:24.351
and the presidential candidates
into the hunted,

01:43:24.440 --> 01:43:27.831
after which ponderous pundits
wonder in mock seriousness

01:43:27.920 --> 01:43:30.151
as to why
some of the best people in this country

01:43:30.240 --> 01:43:32.038
choose not to run for high office.

01:43:34.680 --> 01:43:36.239
Now, politics in this country,

01:43:36.320 --> 01:43:39.040
take it from me,
is on the verge of becoming

01:43:39.120 --> 01:43:41.715
another form of athletic competition,
or sport.

01:43:43.600 --> 01:43:46.957
We'd all better do something
to make this system work,

01:43:47.040 --> 01:43:50.351
or we're all soon gonna be
rephrasing Jefferson to say,

01:43:50.440 --> 01:43:53.672
"I tremble for my country
when I fear we may, in fact,

01:43:53.760 --> 01:43:56.594
"get the kind of leaders we deserve."

01:43:57.960 --> 01:44:00.475
<i>I've said I bend, but I do not break.</i>

01:44:00.560 --> 01:44:03.632
<i>And believe me, I'm not broken.</i>

01:44:03.720 --> 01:44:05.996
<i>I say to my children,</i>

01:44:06.080 --> 01:44:09.118
<i>and the young people of this country,</i>

01:44:09.200 --> 01:44:10.793
<i>I'm angry, too.</i>

01:44:11.440 --> 01:44:13.397
<i>I've made some mistakes. I said so.</i>

01:44:13.480 --> 01:44:16.040
<i>I said I would because I'm human.</i>

01:44:16.720 --> 01:44:18.279
<i>But I'm an idealist,</i>

01:44:19.000 --> 01:44:20.912
<i>and I want to serve my country.</i>

01:44:21.560 --> 01:44:24.029
<i>Events of the past week
should not deter any of you</i>

01:44:24.120 --> 01:44:26.794
<i>who are idealistic young people</i>

01:44:27.440 --> 01:44:30.751
<i>from moving on, from moving up.</i>

01:44:31.280 --> 01:44:34.512
<i>The torch of idealism
in your hearts burns bright.</i>

01:44:34.600 --> 01:44:38.992
<i>It should lead you to want
to make this country better.</i>

01:44:39.600 --> 01:44:42.399
<i>Wherever you go, whatever you do,</i>

01:44:42.480 --> 01:44:45.439
<i>at least in spirit I will be with you.</i>

01:44:45.520 --> 01:44:46.840
<i>Thank you.</i>

